verbose_text: Caspase-1 proteolytically converts newly induced pro interleukin 1 beta (IL-1beta) into its mature form and directs its secretion, triggering pyroptosis and release of non substrate alarmins such as interleukin 1 alpha (IL-1alpha) and HMGB1.
evidence: Caspase-1 proteolytically converts newly induced pro-interleukin 1
